# Cloudflare Workers static-asset headers.
#
# `next.config.js` headers() are honoured by `next dev`, but @cloudflare/next-on-pages
# does NOT reliably emit them for the deployed worker/assets. Without these the
# /ide document is not cross-origin isolated, so `self.crossOriginIsolated` is
# false, SharedArrayBuffer can't be transferred to the WebContainer worker, and
# clicking Run fails with:
#   DataCloneError: SharedArrayBuffer transfer requires self.crossOriginIsolated
#   Error: Unable to create more instances   (failed boot, then retried)
#
# COOP=same-origin + COEP=credentialless enables cross-origin isolation while
# still allowing cross-origin fonts/images to load without CORP headers.
# Keep this in sync with next.config.js headers().
#
# NOTE: this file (and next.config headers()) only reliably cover STATIC /
# prerendered routes under next-on-pages. The dynamically-rendered IDE route
# `/ide/[id]` is SSR, so _headers does not apply to it — its COOP/COEP are set
# in src/middleware.ts (withCoi). Keep all three in sync.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless

# The WebContainer connect handshake tab must NOT be cross-origin isolated, or
# the preview can't complete its postMessage handshake with the IDE. BOTH COOP
# and COEP must be relaxed — COOP:same-origin (from /* above) severs the opener
# bridge setupConnect needs, not just COEP.
# @see https://github.com/stackblitz/webcontainer-core/issues/1725
# (later rule wins for a repeated header, so these override /* above)
/webcontainer/connect/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: unsafe-none
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: unsafe-none

# The service worker script must always be revalidated against the network so a
# new deploy's stamped BUILD_VERSION is picked up promptly. Caching /sw.js (even
# briefly at the CDN edge) delays the update toast. no-cache = store but always
# revalidate; combined with updateViaCache:'none' in PwaUpdateBanner.
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, max-age=0, must-revalidate
